wikipedia_page.main: Kieran Richard Ferguson Parselle (born 1 December 1996) is an English professional football defender who plays for Chippenham Town.

response: The team competes in the Under-18 Football League Youth Alliance. A number of the academy graduates have progressed to the senior squad including Andrew Hughes, Lee Evans, Regan Poole, Aaron Collins, Tom Owen-Evans, Kieran Parselle and Lewis Collins.
Born in Bristol, Owen-Evans was raised in the Forest of Dean. He is childhood friends with fellow Newport academy graduate Kieran Parselle having attended the same school in Bristol.
